quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,"God, the Merciful Benefactor"
  55,2,It is He Who has taught the Quran
  55,3,He has created the human being
  55,4,He has taught him speech
  55,5,The Sun and the Moon follow courses computed
  55,6,And the herbs and the trees both bow in adoration
  55,7,"And the firmament has He raised high, and He has established the balance"
  55,8,In order that you may not transgress the balance
  55,9,"So establish weight with justice, and do not fall short with balance"
  55,10,It is He Who has spread out the earth for His creatures
  55,11,Therein is fruit and date palms producing spathes
  55,12,"Also corn with leaves and stalk for fodder, and sweet-smelling plants"
  55,13,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,14,He created the human being from sounding clay like pottery
  55,15,And He created jinn from fire free of smoke
  55,16,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,17,Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,19,He has let free the two bodies of flowing water meeting together
  55,20,Between them is a barrier that they do not transgress
  55,21,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,22,Out of them come pearls and coral
  55,23,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,24,And His are the ships sailing smoothly through the seas lofty as mountains
  55,25,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny